# These files are vendored into the repos this plugin scaffolds, and those repos travel to
# machines that are not this one. A scaffold performed on Windows must not commit CRLF shell
# scripts that die with `$'\r': command not found` the first time CI runs them on Linux.
#
# This governs the working copy on the *installing* machine, which is the copy shutil.copy2
# hands to the target. It does not retroactively fix blobs already committed with CRLF —
# that took one `git add --renormalize .`.
#
# The catch-all comes first so nothing depends on remembering to add an extension here; the
# explicit lines below are the ones that would actually break, and they are listed because a
# reader should be able to see why this file exists without reconstructing it.
*       text=auto eol=lf
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.tmpl  text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
